verbose_text: The enzymes consist of two domains : (1) the C-terminal YrdC like domain which catalyzes the decomposition of CP to carbamate and phosphate, the carbamate then reacting with ATP to form the carbamyladenylate intermediate and pyrophosphate; and (2) the N-terminal Kae1 like domain which catalyzes the transfer of the carbamyl group from carbamyladenylate to the hydroxyl group of the substrates [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: catalyzes the decomposition of CP to carbamate and phosphate, the carbamate
